<br>
In the end what I find most tragic about this situation, though, is that Zimbabwe is in the heart of a terrible famine and the middle of the growing season when they're doing this, meaning their will a change regime in the middle of the growing season, in many cases from people with generations of experience with the crops to people with pastoral, other crop or no agricultural background.  Tens of thousands will probably starve because of the timing of the execution of this initiative.  That is tragicly irresponsible government making a terrible situation a national disaster.<br>
